[div class=p 
	"The middle tower skip is my favorite part again here I saved 10 seconds just in the execution of this skip, basically in this skip you have to use an enemy to jump higher so you need to get an enemy to a particular/desired spot as fast as possible that's why I  used the already available big guys there and barely waited for any frames there, I also did some manipulation so that's why those enemies ran after me so could get them to the specific spot in the fastest possible time.
	$LF
	"Later two newly discovered skips (thanks to GMP) were used in the upper tower to save 10 seconds.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Final Boss:   In the last movement phase of the fight I found that rotating on the pole is 68 frames faster than jumping off and jumping back to the pole so I used it.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The Mental realm:  The fastest way I found to disappear Dark Prince is just 4 normal attacks + 3 jump kicks or 3 normal attacks + 4 jump kicks, both are same speed so one can use any on them with this I saved 1 second here too. Besides all these I did many other small optimizations throughout the entire game but mentioning all of them is a lot of work so I am avoiding it.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Another really cool thing I learned is the ladder climbing, when climbing the ladder you always slide to the side on top of it but I noticed that you can only do it when your "climbing 1 step" animation is finished (not RTA viable but you can loose upto 30 frames if you are not aware of this) so that's why you always adjust your height when grabing the ladder in such way that your "climbing 1 step" animation is almost finished so that you can slide to the side in blink of an eye, this is the reason why grabbing the ladder as high as prince can is not faster in many cases.
	$LF
]div
